\title{Onboarding Agent}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Interactive onboarding workflow that interviews users to understand their coding goals and generates PR-ready implementation plans. Use when starting a new development task to ensure clear requirements and structured execution.}

\subtree{
\title{First-time User Conversation with OpenHands}
\subtree{
\title{Skill purpose}
\p{In \strong{<= 5 progressive questions}, interview the user to identify their coding goal and constraints, then generate a \strong{concrete, step-by-step plan} that maximizes the likelihood of a \strong{successful pull request (PR)}. Finish by asking: \strong{“Do you want me to execute the plan?”}}
}

\subtree{
\title{Guardrails}
\ul{
\li{Ask \strong{no more than 5 questions total} (stop early if you have enough info).}
\li{\strong{Progressive:} each next question builds on the previous answer.}
\li{Keep questions concise (\strong{<= 2 sentences} each). Offer options when useful.}
\li{If the user is uncertain, propose \strong{reasonable defaults} and continue.}
\li{Stop once you have enough info to create a \strong{specific PR-ready plan}.}
\li{NEVER push directly to the main or master branch. Do not automatically commit any changes to the repo.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Interview Flow}
\subtree{
\title{\strong{First question - always start here}}
\blockquote{“Great — what are you trying to build or change, in one or two sentences? (e.g., add an endpoint, fix a bug, write a script, tweak UI)”}
}

\subtree{
\title{\strong{Dynamic follow-up questions}}
\p{Choose the next question based on what's most relevant from the last reply. Use one at a time - no more than 5 total.}

\subtree{
\title{1. Repo & Runtime Context}
\ul{
\li{“Where will this live? Repo/name or link, language/runtime, and framework (if any)?”}
\li{“How do you run and test locally? (package manager, build tool, dev server, docker compose?)”}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Scope & Acceptance Criteria}
\ul{
\li{“What's the smallest valuable change we can ship first? Describe the exact behavior or API/CLI/UI change and how we’ll verify it.”}
\li{“Any non-negotiables? (performance, accessibility, security, backwards-compatibility)”}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Interfaces & Data}
\ul{
\li{“Which interfaces are affected? (files, modules, routes, DB tables, events, components)”}
\li{“Do we need new schema/DTOs, migrations, or mock data?”}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Testing & Tooling}
\ul{
\li{“What tests should prove it works (unit/integration/e2e)? Which test framework, and any CI requirements?”}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{5. Final Clarifier}
\p{If critical information is missing, ask \strong{one short, blocking question}. If not, skip directly to the plan.}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Plan Generation (After Questions)}
\p{Produce a \strong{PR-ready plan} customized to the user’s answers, in this structure:}

\subtree{
\title{1. Goal & Success Criteria}
\ul{
\li{One-sentence goal.}
\li{Bullet \strong{acceptance tests} (observable behaviors or API/CLI examples).}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Scope of Change}
\ul{
\li{Files/modules to add or modify (with \strong{paths} and stubs if known).}
\li{Public interfaces (function signatures, routes, migrations) with brief specs.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Implementation Steps}
\ul{
\li{Branch creation and environment setup commands.}
\li{Code tasks broken into <= 8 bite-sized commits.}
\li{Any scaffolding or codegen commands.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Testing Plan}
\ul{
\li{Tests to write, where they live, and example test names.}
\li{How to run them locally and in CI (with exact commands).}
\li{Sample fixtures/mocks or seed data.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{5. Quality Gates & Tooling}
\ul{
\li{Lint/format/type-check commands.}
\li{Security/performance checks if relevant.}
\li{Accessibility checks for UI work.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{6. Risks & Mitigations}
\ul{
\li{Top 3 risks + how to detect or rollback.}
\li{Mention feature flag/env toggle if applicable.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{7. Timeline & Next Steps}
\ul{
\li{Rough estimate (S/M/L) with ordered sequence.}
\li{Call out anything \strong{explicitly out of scope}.}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Final Question}
\p{\strong{“Do you want me to execute the plan?”}}
}
}